verbs.description: outwear (third-person singular simple present outwears, present participle outwearing, simple past outwore, past participle outworn)

examples: Crushed impotent beneath this reign of terror,
Dazed with mysteries of woe and error,
The soul is too outworn for wondering.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To outlast; to survive or outlive longer than.
